\begin{abstract}

We investigate to what extend the replica-exchange Monte Carlo method
is able to equilibrate a simple liquid in its supercooled state. We find
that this method does indeed allow to generate accurately the canonical
distribution function even at low temperatures and that its efficiency
is about 10-100 times higher than the usual canonical molecular dynamics
simulation.

\end{abstract}

